Prepare the pasta according to package directions, adding the broccoli, carrot, and bell pepper during the last 5 minutes of cooking. Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the garlic and scallion and cook for 1 minute. Add the shrimp and cook, stirring frequently, for 3 minutes, or until the shrimp are opaque. Add the tomato and cook for 1 minute. Remove from the heat. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the buttermilk, vinegar, flaxseed oil, mustard, black pepper, and salt. Add the shrimp mixture and pasta mixture and toss to coat well.